The certificate and the key file can be crated with the following command:

    $ go run `go env GOROOT`/src/pkg/crypto/tls/generate_cert.go -ca -host="127.0.0.1"

We need to convert the pem files into .go file for embedding into go programs easily.
Install go-bindata with:

    $ go get github.com/jteeuwen/go-bindata

Then we can convert them with the following commands:

    $ go-bindata -uncompressed -pkg=kontrol cert.pem
    $ go-bindata -uncompressed -pkg=kontrol key.pem

Copy the Kontrol Certificate into Kite package:

    $ cp cert.pem.go ../../newkite/kontrol.pem.go

Edit the file and change the package name to "kite".
Then, rename function name to "kontrol_pem".
